data.title: Wings were only so-so
data.text: I went to the Wing Dome in Kirkland, WA specifically to try a variety of their offered wings thinking I might buy some for a future football or family event at my house. I was very disappointed! They claim the wings are deep fried but they had no crunch to them whatsoever, which is one of the main things good wings need, in my opinion. The flavor was okay but without the crunch, why bother? I was not impressed and will not be returning. My search for good wings continues!

data.title: Saucy goodness
data.text:
I was the odd man out of our table of wingers, but the triple garlic chicken salad was very good and would have it again in a heartbeat.

By the pound wings was a hit with the group and the waiter was a kick.

data.title: Sticky like a movie theatre.
data.text:
The place is sticky.   

Kirkland has a really weird food scene.  People from all over come to Kirkland when the weather is nice.   People come to Kirkland on the weekends.   What it creates is this really lame restaurant experience.  The Wing Dome is one of those places.   

The food isn't great and it isn't un edible.   It is quintessential Kirkland.  Do the bare minimum and just rely on the fact that people will come.  

It is what it is.  Just another option of lacking fare.

owner_response.author: Sean M, Public Relations Manager at Wing Dome, responded to this review
owner_response.text: Please accept our apologies. We would be happy to discuss further. Please provide us your email for a manager to contact you directly or contact me at smisday@conrests.com.
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Disappointed
data.text: My husband and I stopped into the restaurant for an early lunch, 12 noon on a weekday.  The restaurant was empty, 6 - 10 customers,.  We were greeted by friendly staff member who sat us.  A few moments later a very friendly waitress came to say hello and offered us some advise on ordering wings and beer as it was our first visit to this chain.  We ordered wings as an appetizer,  my husband ordered a cheeseburger with waffle type fries. I ordered a shrimp Po-boy with fries.    The wings were standard , nothing so special to have a restaurant named after them.  The cheeseburger was tasteless ( frozen thin burger?). The waffle fries ( I think they called them Chips?) were soggy and Luke warm.  My Shrimp Po-boy was ok.  I enjoyed the spicy batter, and my fries had a bad oil taste to them.   I'd have to say we did not complain not giving them a chance to compensate us by fixing our complaints.  We just weren't in the mood to complain to the lovely waitress that was very competent and it wasn't her fault.   Plus at this point we weren't hungry enough to order a new meal.    One more thing; being it was only 12:00 and people usually like to talk at lunch, we found it weird the volume of the music was to loud to speak without yelling at one another.  Our waitress came thru and had the volume lowered a bit.

data.title: Went above and beyond to solve an issue
data.text: My husband considers himself a wing expert and his favorite place by far is The Wing Dome.  Unfortunately we live over an hour away from the closest one so he only gets them a few times a year.  Last week was his birthday so I ordered some online and stopped and got them on my way home.  Get them home and he opens the boxes only to find they have forgotten to sauce them so they are just plain dry wings.  He was so disappointed that I suggested he call and tell them what happened.  He did spoke to a manger who apologized profusely and then offered him a $50 gift card to get more wings.  I ordered and picked them up today and the manager personally apologized and made sure the order was right before he gave it to me.  Great service and great wings....can't beat that!

data.title: Small wings
data.text: We popped in around 6.30pm on a Wednesday.  On arriving nobody really came to seat us, we waited around 5 min. at the entrance, until a guy came and said, just pick your seats.  By this time, all we really wanted to do is order, pick up the wings and leave.  The place felt cold and grubby inside, they had uncomfortable metal chairs.  The menu was also not very easy to understand, some flavours e.g. garlic don't allow you to pick a heat level, normally at other restaurants you can pick a flavour like bbq or garlic and a heat level, such as extra spicy.  Staff here, were not too friendly.  We took the wings home.  The flavour of garlic on the wings was fine, but they were not spicy enough, and we felt the wings were too small.  The menu makes you feel like, the portion will be bigger, than it actually is.  I don't think paying over $1 for each wing, is good value for money, considering they are sooo tiny.

data.title: Good local wing restaurant
data.text:
OK, this is my comfort food restaurant.  You buy the wings by the pound.  Typically, it takes two pounds for me and probably one pound will be sufficient for most women.

They have a pretty good sauce selection with heat up to melt your stomach hot.  The beer selection is reasonable but not exceptionally extensive. The servers are friendly and efficient.  

They have TVs all over the place in case you need a sports fix.

data.title: If you like Wings, this is the place on the Eastside!
data.text:
Wings and other fried things with hot sauce.
Food is greasy, which they make no bones about, but as it should be.
Recommend the Wings extra crispy, with the hot sauce 3 or 4 or 5 star, or try the Peanut Sambal sauce for something different. 
Local beers on tap.
Family friendly, but also good for after work adult or sports events.

data.title: Yummy wings and great service
data.text: We have been very regular visitors for several years. My personal favorite are the #5 wings. The spice levels are sometimes a bit inconsistent but mostly good. It's a very lively place with friendly staff. Customer service is great.

data.title: Sodium Packed
data.text: I know wings aren't even close to being a healthy food choice but the ones at wing dome are even more so. They're SO SALTY. Even the boys were downing water after every bite. And we all got sick hours after. Horrible experience and won't be going back. Stay away - the drive to BWW in Seattle is worth it.

data.title: Awesome Wings!
data.text:
Went for my periodic wing fix (being from Buffalo, NY,, I feel the need regularly).
The wings were done to perfection, crispy and coated with spice.
Onion rings good, beer selection is nice, as well.

data.title: Best Wings in Kirkland
data.text: Staff is friendly and wings are great! Get there early on game days or you will have to wait! The bar was a nice add with additional seating. Burgers are great as well if you are not a wing person. I add the wedge salad to help with the hot wings!

data.title: Great neighborhood wing joint
data.text: Great variety of wings, fun and energetic atmosphere.  Could use a bit more staff on busy nights, as servers (while gracious) can appear overworked.

data.title: #TNF
data.text:
It was Thursday night football, what better than Wings and beer to celebrate the NYG game. 

Wings were great I had buffalo wings with a Guinness

data.title: Wings in heart of Kirkland
data.text: The location is off the main drag so parking is better then most places. The building and atmosphere is great for a sporting event as is the selection of drafts. Unfortunately the wings are rather small but well spiced. So might need to order more if you are a hungry wing aficionado.

data.title: Nice People, Nice Sports Bar Vibe, Tastylicious Wings
data.text:
Been a Wing Dome customer since their early days in Seattle (Wallingford) in the mid 1990s. Still my go-to hot wing spot when I visit the Emerald City.

Kirkland location - friend servers, casual atmosphere, very family friendly.  Was there on NFC Championship Sunday so business was brisk/busy on sit-down and carry-out.  We ate a lite snack (delicious sweet potato fries and a lovely garden salad) while waiting for the to-go wing order.  

Go there.  Try all the sauces.  You'll thank me and smile.

data.title: Pain! Pain! Pain!
data.text: I visited the wing dome and had a fun time! A wing above the 4 or 5 level can be very spicy, and it would be better to start with a specialty wing or a 3. If you are to order a specialty, I would recommend a garlic specialty in a kids size. The service was great and we saw someone complete the 7 challenge. Good food, Good service!

data.title: finally service !
data.text: We are new to Washington and I am always disappointing in the service we get. Our server was so busy but he still took the time and talk to us, He was kind to my kids and it was a nice outing for us. The food is good, not out of this world but we will go back over and over because we were taken care of

data.title: Good Place to Watch a Game
data.text: If you're looking for wings and all the permutations that come from wings..boneless, hot, strips, etc...and you want to watch a game, this is a great place.  Good food, good drinks, good service.  Typical sports bar kind of tables and chairs, but fast, attentive service, even when crowed.  Beer is cold, wings are HOT.

data.title: What's not to  like?
data.text: Good wings with lots of choices, fair beer selection but weak on local micros, and a sports bar atmosphere. All in all a good place on game day.
